WEBVTT

1
00:01:41.819 --> 00:01:42.950
salute you.

2
00:03:57.889 --> 00:03:59.955
Be gentle. Hanno.

3
00:05:23.711 --> 00:05:26.513
We invoke you
by your great names

4
00:05:26.514 --> 00:05:28.339
to come to our aid.

5
00:05:28.340 --> 00:05:30.077
Defeat the Romans.

6
00:05:30.078 --> 00:05:31.749
Destroy their ships.

7
00:05:31.750 --> 00:05:33.487
their engines of war.

8
00:05:33.488 --> 00:05:35.412
and their soldiers.

9
00:05:35.413 --> 00:05:38.427
We will prevail.

10
00:05:43.423 --> 00:05:45.225
Ozalsces.

11
00:05:47.801 --> 00:05:49.361
Arishat.

12
00:06:03.751 --> 00:06:05.047
Hanno.

13
00:06:08.415 --> 00:06:11.492
You did not make
an offering today.

14
00:06:11.493 --> 00:06:13.989
I prefer to sacrifice a Roman.

15
00:06:29.744 --> 00:06:31.106
Where you are.

16
00:06:32.241 --> 00:06:33.207
I am. too.

17
00:06:37.180 --> 00:06:38.915
And where you are.

18
00:06:38.916 --> 00:06:41.951
I am. too. forever.

19
00:06:41.952 --> 00:06:43.382
My wife.

20
00:07:19.090 --> 00:07:21.826
The wind is too strong.
Furl sail and strike water.

21
00:07:21.827 --> 00:07:24.224
Furl sail.
strike water!

22
00:07:24.225 --> 00:07:26.325
Furl sail
and strike water!

23
00:07:34.532 --> 00:07:36.611
Strike water!

24
00:08:03.937 --> 00:08:07.003
They have no lands
but the ones they've stolen.

25
00:08:07.004 --> 00:08:09.775
Wherever they go.
they leave destruction

26
00:08:09.776 --> 00:08:11.437
and call it peace.

27
00:08:13.375 --> 00:08:16.112
This is the last free city
in Africa Nova.

28
00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:20.314
Today. we go into battle.

29
00:08:21.724 --> 00:08:26.352
Pray that your god
is with you.
If he is not. he is no god.

30
00:08:29.424 --> 00:08:31.698
We've nothing to fear.

31
00:08:31.699 --> 00:08:33.602
Where death is. we are not.

32
00:08:34.528 --> 00:08:36.033
Where we are.

33
00:08:37.630 --> 00:08:38.871
death is not.

34
00:08:41.469 --> 00:08:43.138
Stay together and listen
for my commands.

35
00:08:46.815 --> 00:08:49.475
Your eyes up
and your head out.

36
00:09:24.820 --> 00:09:26.952
Fire!

37
00:09:31.794 --> 00:09:35.256
Ready your weapons!

38
00:09:35.257 --> 00:09:36.390
Again!

39
00:09:42.464 --> 00:09:44.332
We're ablaze on the right!

40
00:09:45.632 --> 00:09:47.434
Keep formation!

41
00:09:51.143 --> 00:09:52.780
Pull!

42
00:09:59.151 --> 00:10:00.820
Archers ready.

43
00:10:00.821 --> 00:10:02.383
Release!

44
00:10:09.557 --> 00:10:10.764
Nock!

45
00:10:10.765 --> 00:10:13.162
Draw!

46
00:10:13.163 --> 00:10:14.395
Loose!

47
00:10:21.503 --> 00:10:22.634
Archers!

48
00:10:30.743 --> 00:10:32.380
Fire!

49
00:10:43.899 --> 00:10:46.900
Raise the tower!
Raise the tower!

50
00:11:02.918 --> 00:11:05.379
Back astern!
Back astern!

51
00:11:12.422 --> 00:11:14.257
Keep cranking.

52
00:11:24.269 --> 00:11:26.070
Drop drawbridge!

53
00:11:26.071 --> 00:11:27.731
The drawbridge is stuck!

54
00:11:37.315 --> 00:11:38.710
Sir!

55
00:11:41.187 --> 00:11:42.351
Loose!

56
00:11:54.134 --> 00:11:55.694
Back.

57
00:12:58.495 --> 00:12:59.999
Archers!

58
00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:01.198
There!

59
00:13:01.199 --> 00:13:02.530
Kill her!

60
00:13:03.401 --> 00:13:04.697
Arishat!

61
00:14:14.736 --> 00:14:16.736
Arishat.

62
00:14:28.090 --> 00:14:32.191
Arishat!

63
00:14:39.363 --> 00:14:41.299
I'll wait for you.

64
00:15:24.344 --> 00:15:26.244
Check all the bodies!

65
00:15:26.245 --> 00:15:28.115
Leave nothing!

66
00:17:16.951 --> 00:17:18.654
I claim this city...

67
00:17:21.461 --> 00:17:23.362
for the glory of Rome.

68
00:17:25.267 --> 00:17:26.959
<I>Vae victis.</I>

69
00:17:29.832 --> 00:17:31.469
Woe to the conquered.

70
00:17:50.554 --> 00:17:51.686
Next!

71
00:17:54.393 --> 00:17:55.460
Move it!

72
00:18:11.203 --> 00:18:14.380
Down the stairs!
Downstairs!

73
00:19:01.561 --> 00:19:04.660
Hey.

74
00:19:04.661 --> 00:19:06.893
What damage have they
done you. eh?

75
00:19:19.678 --> 00:19:21.743
Lift it up. Easy. easy.

76
00:19:21.744 --> 00:19:24.141
Hold that.

77
00:19:29.952 --> 00:19:31.292
Arishat?

78
00:19:34.627 --> 00:19:36.022
I am sorry. my son.

79
00:19:39.566 --> 00:19:41.192
I have not long.

80
00:19:42.569 --> 00:19:44.634
This galley

81
00:19:44.635 --> 00:19:47.098
is sailing us to something
I cannot endure.

82
00:19:47.099 --> 00:19:50.343
I am ready... to be taken
to another place.

83
00:19:50.344 --> 00:19:52.543
Stay here a while longer.

84
00:19:55.813 --> 00:20:00.551
I remember well
when you first
were brought to us.

85
00:20:00.552 --> 00:20:03.719
A lonely boy
from the desert.
Guileless.

86
00:20:03.720 --> 00:20:04.952
Afraid.

87
00:20:06.087 --> 00:20:09.187
You embraced everything
we taught you.

88
00:20:11.466 --> 00:20:15.600
You found Arishat's love.
Your soul was replenished.

89
00:20:16.867 --> 00:20:20.197
When I die.

90
00:20:20.198 --> 00:20:23.036
my ancestors will meet me
in the next world.

91
00:20:25.172 --> 00:20:26.511
Who will meet you?

92
00:20:26.512 --> 00:20:28.876
Hanno.

93
00:20:28.877 --> 00:20:30.812
I am done.

94
00:20:30.813 --> 00:20:34.146
Do not let them change
what you are.

95
00:21:05.817 --> 00:21:07.013
Have you seen this boy?

96
00:21:12.318 --> 00:21:14.527
Eama! Eama!

97
00:21:19.897 --> 00:21:22.326
You must
go alone now. Hanno.

98
00:21:26.002 --> 00:21:27.903
Never let them find you.

99
00:21:32.545 --> 00:21:34.514
Go. Go.

100
00:23:27.519 --> 00:23:30.893
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

101
00:23:30.894 --> 00:23:32.159
Emperor Geta.

102
00:23:34.460 --> 00:23:36.130
Emperor Caracalla.

103
00:23:37.705 --> 00:23:39.363
General Acacius.

104
00:23:39.364 --> 00:23:42.465
I have taken Numidia
in your names

105
00:23:42.466 --> 00:23:44.401
that your dominion
may eclipse that

106
00:23:44.402 --> 00:23:46.678
of every emperor
that came before you.

107
00:23:46.679 --> 00:23:49.176
Crown him with laurels. brother.

108
00:23:58.086 --> 00:24:01.287
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

109
00:24:06.866 --> 00:24:08.767
In honor
of your conquest.

110
00:24:09.737 --> 00:24:11.869
there will be games
in the Colosseum.

111
00:24:13.070 --> 00:24:15.707
I require no games
in my honor.

112
00:24:15.708 --> 00:24:19.370
Serving the Senate
and the people of Rome

113
00:24:19.371 --> 00:24:21.174
is honor enough for me.

114
00:24:21.175 --> 00:24:24.045
You are too modest.
Acacius.

115
00:24:24.046 --> 00:24:27.214
It does not suit a general
as accomplished as yourself.

116
00:24:29.416 --> 00:24:32.317
The glory is yours.
not mine.

117
00:24:32.318 --> 00:24:35.518
I only ask for
some respite from war

118
00:24:35.519 --> 00:24:37.091
to spend time
with my wife.

119
00:24:37.092 --> 00:24:39.632
Your wife. yes.

120
00:24:39.633 --> 00:24:41.392
Remember the privileges
we have granted her?

121
00:24:42.834 --> 00:24:45.033
Where is she now
to ignore such an occasion?

122
00:24:45.034 --> 00:24:47.773
There are victories
yet still to come.

123
00:24:49.436 --> 00:24:50.941
Persia.

124
00:24:52.307 --> 00:24:53.338
India.

125
00:24:54.571 --> 00:24:58.080
Both... must be conquered.

126
00:25:00.018 --> 00:25:02.622
Rome has so many subjects.

127
00:25:02.623 --> 00:25:04.548
She must feed them.

128
00:25:05.793 --> 00:25:08.057
They can eat war.

129
00:25:10.930 --> 00:25:14.063
Your triumphs
will be celebrated

130
00:25:14.901 --> 00:25:17.297
as a tribute
to the greatness

131
00:25:18.069 --> 00:25:19.398
of the Roman people.

132
00:25:41.763 --> 00:25:42.828
Go to hell!

133
00:26:03.015 --> 00:26:05.476
Macrinus of Thysdrus.

134
00:26:05.477 --> 00:26:07.786
master of gladiators!

135
00:26:30.238 --> 00:26:32.173
Stay close.

136
00:26:48.454 --> 00:26:52.260
Aediles
and the town councilors.

137
00:26:52.999 --> 00:26:55.560
distinguished guests.

138
00:26:56.662 --> 00:26:58.661
citizens of Antium.

139
00:27:02.239 --> 00:27:04.602
behold the fate

140
00:27:06.012 --> 00:27:08.573
of the conquered enemies
of Rome:

141
00:27:09.917 --> 00:27:14.722
The barbarian Numidians
and their chieftain.

142
00:27:15.516 --> 00:27:18.483
Jugurtha!

143
00:28:38.665 --> 00:28:40.070
This one is interesting.

144
00:29:06.792 --> 00:29:08.296
I'll buy him.

145
00:29:29.188 --> 00:29:32.453
Halt! Who goes there?

146
00:29:33.995 --> 00:29:35.225
General.

147
00:30:10.724 --> 00:30:12.295
My lady.

148
00:30:20.536 --> 00:30:22.942
I thank the gods
that brought you back home safe.

149
00:30:22.943 --> 00:30:26.078
Thank the Army.
They protected me.

150
00:30:27.807 --> 00:30:29.015
Mm.

151
00:30:30.051 --> 00:30:31.710
Let me feed you.

152
00:30:59.410 --> 00:31:00.442
Go.

153
00:31:01.148 --> 00:31:02.543
To the wall.

154
00:31:13.325 --> 00:31:15.753
The arena
is a sacred temple.

155
00:31:15.754 --> 00:31:17.458
For the bravest of you.

156
00:31:17.459 --> 00:31:20.428
the road to glory
runs through the arena.

157
00:31:20.429 --> 00:31:22.562
The arena turns slaves
into gladiators

158
00:31:22.563 --> 00:31:24.466
and gladiators into free men.

159
00:31:31.772 --> 00:31:33.310
You have worms.

160
00:31:37.283 --> 00:31:40.679
I know this one.
He eats monkeys.

161
00:31:54.828 --> 00:31:57.136
Go. Sit. Eat.

162
00:32:57.759 --> 00:32:58.791
You.

163
00:33:00.234 --> 00:33:02.597
Hanno. get up.

164
00:33:08.539 --> 00:33:12.640
What is
your native language?
I speak them all.

165
00:33:16.250 --> 00:33:19.449
You don't answer because
you can't or because you won't?

166
00:33:21.618 --> 00:33:22.880
Mm. all right.

167
00:33:22.881 --> 00:33:26.752
Violence...
is the universal language.

168
00:33:26.753 --> 00:33:29.524
Viggo.
put him through his paces.

169
00:33:29.525 --> 00:33:33.430
He can fight an ape.
Let's see if he
can fight a man.

170
00:34:43.304 --> 00:34:44.402
Enough!

171
00:34:48.969 --> 00:34:50.133
Very good.

172
00:34:51.642 --> 00:34:53.004
Very good.

173
00:34:55.041 --> 00:34:56.414
Hose him down.

174
00:35:00.211 --> 00:35:01.650
Bring him to me.

175
00:35:08.659 --> 00:35:09.955
Ah!

176
00:35:12.894 --> 00:35:14.597
A strong jaw.

177
00:35:16.403 --> 00:35:17.896
Good arms.

178
00:35:19.371 --> 00:35:20.767
Better smell.

179
00:35:23.740 --> 00:35:25.311
You will do well.

180
00:35:26.072 --> 00:35:28.005
It is an art.

181
00:35:28.006 --> 00:35:29.876
choosing gladiators.

182
00:35:31.352 --> 00:35:33.648
Some choose entertainers.

183
00:35:33.649 --> 00:35:35.815
Some choose brute force.

184
00:35:35.816 --> 00:35:37.290
I choose rage.

185
00:35:41.758 --> 00:35:43.361
Crowd loves blood.

186
00:35:43.362 --> 00:35:45.220
And they love those who
love blood as much as they do.

187
00:35:45.221 --> 00:35:47.696
And you. my friend. rage

188
00:35:48.435 --> 00:35:50.633
pours out of you like...

189
00:35:52.098 --> 00:35:53.669
like milk...

190
00:35:55.266 --> 00:35:56.573
from a whore's tit.

191
00:35:57.609 --> 00:35:59.410
You will be
quite the fighter.

192
00:35:59.411 --> 00:36:01.038
Not for you.

193
00:36:01.039 --> 00:36:03.205
You're right.
you do not fight for me.

194
00:36:03.206 --> 00:36:05.680
I put you in the ring.
you fight or you die.

195
00:36:05.681 --> 00:36:06.912
The choice is yours.

196
00:36:06.913 --> 00:36:09.948
But whose head
could I give you

197
00:36:09.949 --> 00:36:13.688
that would satisfy this fury?

198
00:36:13.689 --> 00:36:15.690
The entire Roman Army's.

199
00:36:19.125 --> 00:36:20.299
Too much.

200
00:36:20.300 --> 00:36:22.026
Mm.

201
00:36:22.027 --> 00:36:24.193
The general will do.

202
00:36:24.194 --> 00:36:25.129
General?

203
00:36:26.572 --> 00:36:28.539
General Acacius?
Mm.

204
00:36:30.840 --> 00:36:33.444
Use your rage
in my service.

205
00:36:33.445 --> 00:36:37.317
and you will have his head
ready for your sword.

206
00:36:38.584 --> 00:36:41.618
Serve me and I will serve you.
Deny me...

207
00:36:42.984 --> 00:36:45.588
and you will die.

208
00:36:48.495 --> 00:36:50.362
There are times I wished
you'd abandoned me

209
00:36:50.363 --> 00:36:52.221
rather than
fight their wars.

210
00:36:52.222 --> 00:36:54.224
I've made my choice.

211
00:36:56.261 --> 00:36:58.129
I can live with it.

212
00:37:02.267 --> 00:37:05.169
But my patience with those two
is at an end.

213
00:37:08.009 --> 00:37:10.239
Leta?

214
00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:13.782
You may go
to your quarters now.
We need nothing more.

215
00:37:20.956 --> 00:37:22.625
To hear wives and mothers
mourning their dead

216
00:37:22.626 --> 00:37:24.364
on that beach at Numidia...

217
00:37:26.896 --> 00:37:28.533
Lucilla.

218
00:37:33.672 --> 00:37:35.133
No more.

219
00:37:37.544 --> 00:37:39.675
I will not waste

220
00:37:39.676 --> 00:37:43.273
another generation
of young men for their vanity.

221
00:37:45.486 --> 00:37:49.015
If I fight another campaign.
it must be to depose them.

222
00:37:50.953 --> 00:37:53.019
When will your troops
arrive?

223
00:37:53.857 --> 00:37:56.252
They land at Ostia
in ten days.

224
00:37:56.253 --> 00:38:00.224
How many of them will be
loyal to you alone?

225
00:38:01.898 --> 00:38:03.293
All of them.

226
00:38:05.363 --> 00:38:09.034
The emperors do not have
the support of the people.

227
00:38:09.035 --> 00:38:13.809
The people are weary
of the madness. the tyranny.

228
00:38:16.812 --> 00:38:20.915
What is the dream of Rome
if her people are not free?

229
00:38:43.368 --> 00:38:45.906
Enjoy yourself.
everyone.

230
00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:47.974
to excess!

231
00:38:47.975 --> 00:38:51.010
Thank you. Thank you.

232
00:39:02.926 --> 00:39:04.189
Oh!

233
00:39:04.928 --> 00:39:08.060
Please. drink.

234
00:39:08.061 --> 00:39:10.932
Ah! Excuse me. Macrinus!

235
00:39:12.265 --> 00:39:15.001
I knew the provinces
were not enough for you.

236
00:39:15.002 --> 00:39:18.235
I'm just here
for the games.
Ah. well.

237
00:39:18.236 --> 00:39:19.940
you won't be disappointed.

238
00:39:19.941 --> 00:39:23.240
Rome has all the games
that men like you like to play.

239
00:39:23.241 --> 00:39:25.583
Men like me. Thraex?
Men like us.

240
00:39:25.584 --> 00:39:29.213
I know nothing happens
in Rome unless you've
tasted it first.

241
00:39:45.705 --> 00:39:47.297
What is my purpose here?

242
00:39:47.298 --> 00:39:48.772
You'll find out soon enough.

243
00:39:53.372 --> 00:39:55.613
What's this we hear
about you being interested

244
00:39:55.614 --> 00:39:59.441
in standing for election
to the Senate. Macrinus?

245
00:39:59.442 --> 00:40:02.048
Me? No. I'm. uh...

246
00:40:02.049 --> 00:40:04.622
I don't even know how
to use an abacus.

247
00:40:04.623 --> 00:40:06.350
But I do understand that

248
00:40:07.628 --> 00:40:08.989
it's customary
for your guests

249
00:40:08.990 --> 00:40:11.728
to make wagers
at these affairs?

250
00:40:11.729 --> 00:40:13.962
How large a sum
did you have in mind?

251
00:40:15.603 --> 00:40:17.129
A thousand gold denarii?

252
00:40:17.130 --> 00:40:18.461
Two.

253
00:40:20.399 --> 00:40:21.640
Two?

254
00:40:23.611 --> 00:40:25.842
Denarii.

255
00:40:41.761 --> 00:40:44.487
Stand back! Stand back!

256
00:40:46.194 --> 00:40:47.665
My emperors.

257
00:40:47.666 --> 00:40:51.834
Lords. ladies and gentlemen.
and senators.

258
00:40:51.835 --> 00:40:54.167
For your entertainment.

259
00:40:54.873 --> 00:40:57.235
the art of combat!

260
00:40:59.304 --> 00:41:01.074
May I present

261
00:41:01.075 --> 00:41:03.274
the barbarian versus.

262
00:41:03.275 --> 00:41:07.509
from my own stable.
the mighty Vichek!

263
00:41:14.695 --> 00:41:17.256
This is your gladiator?
It is.

264
00:41:20.734 --> 00:41:23.360
Three rounds.
hand to hand.

265
00:41:23.361 --> 00:41:25.065
Swords!

266
00:41:25.066 --> 00:41:28.366
We want swords.
A fight to the death.

267
00:41:29.710 --> 00:41:32.743
No quarter to be offered...
or given.

268
00:41:32.744 --> 00:41:34.878
Fight now!

269
00:41:40.347 --> 00:41:41.445
Brother.

270
00:41:42.580 --> 00:41:44.414
let's not kill each other
for their amusement.

271
00:42:50.648 --> 00:42:52.252
Remarkable!

272
00:42:54.694 --> 00:42:56.289
Remarkable!

273
00:42:57.490 --> 00:42:59.490
Thraex.
he looked expensive.

274
00:43:00.834 --> 00:43:03.032
Congratulations.
Thank you.

275
00:43:04.002 --> 00:43:05.364
Remarkable.

276
00:43:09.942 --> 00:43:11.469
From where do you hail?

277
00:43:17.213 --> 00:43:18.476
Speak.

278
00:43:22.152 --> 00:43:23.414
I said speak.

279
00:43:23.415 --> 00:43:25.185
He is from the colonies.
Your Majesty.

280
00:43:25.186 --> 00:43:27.551
His native tongue
is all he understands.

281
00:43:34.065 --> 00:43:37.066
"The gates of hell
are open night and day.

282
00:43:38.597 --> 00:43:43.666
Smooth is the descent.
and easy is the way.

283
00:43:46.407 --> 00:43:48.748
But...

284
00:43:51.016 --> 00:43:53.015
to come back from hell

285
00:43:53.016 --> 00:43:54.951
and view the cheerful skies.

286
00:43:54.952 --> 00:43:59.517
in this the task
and mighty labor lies."

287
00:44:06.064 --> 00:44:07.393
Virgil. Your Majesty.

288
00:44:08.528 --> 00:44:09.559
Poetry!

289
00:44:12.906 --> 00:44:15.500
Very clever. Macrinus.
Thank you.

290
00:44:16.844 --> 00:44:19.206
I've grown so bored.
but you surprise me.

291
00:44:19.207 --> 00:44:22.341
To amuse you is my only wish.

292
00:44:22.342 --> 00:44:24.179
We are amused.
we are amused.

293
00:44:26.216 --> 00:44:27.479
We are amused.

294
00:44:28.922 --> 00:44:32.055
And we all look forward
to seeing your poet

295
00:44:33.124 --> 00:44:34.518
perform in the arena.

296
00:44:34.519 --> 00:44:37.456
As do I. Your Majesties.

297
00:44:38.261 --> 00:44:39.293
Thank you.

298
00:44:39.933 --> 00:44:40.800
Viggo?

299
00:44:42.232 --> 00:44:43.594
Come with me.

300
00:45:01.746 --> 00:45:04.219
You fought well today.
but you were lucky. too.

301
00:45:06.619 --> 00:45:09.124
The lines you recited.

302
00:45:09.125 --> 00:45:11.655
You didn't learn that
in Africa. I know that.

303
00:45:12.625 --> 00:45:14.899
A good verse travels far.
Mm.

304
00:45:14.900 --> 00:45:16.934
Who taught you poetry?

305
00:45:16.935 --> 00:45:19.167
A captured Roman officer.

306
00:45:19.168 --> 00:45:22.566
I was posted guard over him
and he used to tell us tales

307
00:45:22.567 --> 00:45:24.437
to pass the time.

308
00:45:25.407 --> 00:45:26.702
And what became
of this prisoner?

309
00:45:26.703 --> 00:45:28.177
Oh. we ate him.

310
00:45:29.543 --> 00:45:30.640
As barbarians do.

311
00:45:30.641 --> 00:45:33.115
As barbarians do.

312
00:45:33.116 --> 00:45:35.183
And where were you born?

313
00:45:35.184 --> 00:45:37.581
Why does my past matter
if it is my future

314
00:45:37.582 --> 00:45:39.782
to die for you in the arena?

315
00:45:46.527 --> 00:45:48.659
Tell me what use have I
for Roman money.

316
00:45:51.939 --> 00:45:53.466
A gladiator

317
00:45:54.370 --> 00:45:56.139
can buy his own freedom.

318
00:45:57.175 --> 00:45:59.010
His liberty.

319
00:45:59.914 --> 00:46:01.704
The Roman dream.

320
00:46:01.705 --> 00:46:03.838
No. the slave dreams
not of freedom

321
00:46:03.839 --> 00:46:06.314
but of a slave
to call his own.

322
00:46:07.185 --> 00:46:08.646
Cicero.

323
00:46:09.847 --> 00:46:12.221
Is that what you were
raised on. Macrinus?

324
00:46:13.928 --> 00:46:16.489
What did you have to do
for Roman money?

325
00:46:17.822 --> 00:46:19.425
You promised me a head.

326
00:46:19.426 --> 00:46:22.231
Earn your keep
and you can have
anyone's head.

327
00:46:46.488 --> 00:46:48.355
Father.

328
00:46:48.356 --> 00:46:50.853
protect us and guide us.

329
00:47:04.737 --> 00:47:06.110
Senators.

330
00:47:06.739 --> 00:47:07.947
My lady.

331
00:47:13.988 --> 00:47:17.517
My lady. I wish we were
meeting in better times.

332
00:47:18.355 --> 00:47:20.388
Better times will come.

333
00:47:21.655 --> 00:47:24.094
And why are we here?

334
00:47:24.095 --> 00:47:26.031
To take back the city.

335
00:47:27.859 --> 00:47:31.432
And restore Rome
to where she should be.

336
00:47:32.864 --> 00:47:34.732
An exciting venture.

337
00:47:35.966 --> 00:47:38.439
When?
On the final day
of the games.

338
00:47:39.409 --> 00:47:42.244
My army waits for my command
at Ostia.

339
00:47:42.245 --> 00:47:44.984
Five thousand soldiers
loyal to me...

340
00:47:46.482 --> 00:47:48.910
will enter Rome
and then the Colosseum.

341
00:47:48.911 --> 00:47:50.912
where they will
arrest the emperors

342
00:47:50.913 --> 00:47:52.585
for their crimes
against the Senate

343
00:47:53.456 --> 00:47:54.994
and their people.

344
00:47:55.953 --> 00:48:00.999
Uh. this plan
is ambitious and risky.

345
00:48:01.000 --> 00:48:03.859
Rome will be yours
to administer and to—

346
00:48:03.860 --> 00:48:08.600
Marcus Aurelius talked
of restoring power
to the Senate.

347
00:48:08.601 --> 00:48:13.044
but that was a generation ago.
Much has changed.

348
00:48:13.045 --> 00:48:17.048
The people
have not seen hope

349
00:48:17.049 --> 00:48:18.478
for many years.

350
00:48:18.479 --> 00:48:22.251
But with time...
and guidance...

351
00:48:23.781 --> 00:48:27.289
Lucilla. you are the daughter
of Marcus Aurelius.

352
00:48:27.290 --> 00:48:29.358
He had my loyalty.

353
00:48:31.131 --> 00:48:33.098
And so do you.

354
00:48:35.366 --> 00:48:36.827
Senator Thraex?

355
00:48:38.567 --> 00:48:41.964
Politics follows power.
my lady.

356
00:48:43.077 --> 00:48:46.144
Take back
what is rightfully yours...

357
00:48:47.147 --> 00:48:49.180
and the Senate
will support you.

358
00:48:50.282 --> 00:48:51.479
Thank you.

359
00:49:07.596 --> 00:49:08.991
Food! Food!

360
00:49:13.635 --> 00:49:16.107
When I was told of this place.

361
00:49:16.108 --> 00:49:18.308
they never mentioned
the stink.

362
00:49:20.246 --> 00:49:21.508
That would be Hanno.

363
00:49:24.776 --> 00:49:27.679
Well. you'll have to
put up with me as I am.

364
00:49:32.786 --> 00:49:35.886
And what's that up there?
A wolf?

365
00:49:37.659 --> 00:49:40.923
The twins there.
they were outcasts.

366
00:49:40.924 --> 00:49:42.662
Left in the hills to die.

367
00:49:44.171 --> 00:49:47.766
That wolf found them
and she suckled them
on her milk.

368
00:49:49.066 --> 00:49:51.439
Raised by an animal.
It's in their blood.

369
00:49:51.440 --> 00:49:54.344
How do you know this place?

370
00:49:55.512 --> 00:49:57.512
I know the chaos
they brought.

371
00:49:58.746 --> 00:50:01.581
This city infects
everything it touches.

372
00:50:01.582 --> 00:50:03.748
I never dreamt
it would be so big.

373
00:50:03.749 --> 00:50:05.585
Don't fall for it.

374
00:50:05.586 --> 00:50:07.621
This city is diseased.

375
00:50:08.954 --> 00:50:11.097
Food! Food!

376
00:50:34.815 --> 00:50:37.288
You! Barbarian scum!

377
00:50:43.230 --> 00:50:45.230
Help me.
Please. help me!

378
00:51:21.994 --> 00:51:23.268
Ah!
Thraex.

379
00:51:27.098 --> 00:51:28.162
About our wager.

380
00:51:28.163 --> 00:51:29.999
Ah. The barbarian.

381
00:51:30.000 --> 00:51:31.440
Yes. I haven't forgotten.
I always repay my debts.

382
00:51:31.441 --> 00:51:33.376
I was merely
going to suggest

383
00:51:33.377 --> 00:51:35.444
that perhaps your luck
might change.

384
00:51:35.445 --> 00:51:37.843
Shall we say
double or quits?

385
00:51:42.388 --> 00:51:43.617
Ah.
Ah.

386
00:51:55.863 --> 00:51:57.236
Get back!

387
00:52:11.516 --> 00:52:13.043
Fresh meat.

388
00:52:17.082 --> 00:52:18.983
Line up! Line up!

389
00:52:49.587 --> 00:52:52.181
Play! Play!

390
00:53:07.407 --> 00:53:09.704
Emperor Caracalla.

391
00:53:10.410 --> 00:53:12.376
Emperor Geta.

392
00:53:12.377 --> 00:53:15.071
Citizens of Rome!

393
00:53:16.942 --> 00:53:20.076
These sacred games

394
00:53:20.077 --> 00:53:23.420
are held to honor
the victory of Rome

395
00:53:23.421 --> 00:53:26.588
over the barbarians of Numidia.

396
00:53:27.788 --> 00:53:30.395
Go! Go!

397
00:53:33.257 --> 00:53:36.796
And to honor
Rome's legionary commander.

398
00:53:36.797 --> 00:53:39.095
General Justus Acacius!

399
00:53:39.096 --> 00:53:41.867
Long live Acacius!

400
00:53:41.868 --> 00:53:43.407
And with him

401
00:53:43.408 --> 00:53:48.170
Lucilla. the daughter
of Emperor Marcus Aurelius.

402
00:53:49.909 --> 00:53:53.451
Lucilla!
Mother of Rome!

403
00:53:54.421 --> 00:53:55.750
Acacius.

404
00:53:56.423 --> 00:53:57.455
General.

405
00:54:05.089 --> 00:54:08.498
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

406
00:54:08.499 --> 00:54:13.603
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

407
00:54:14.540 --> 00:54:15.637
Speak to them.

408
00:54:15.638 --> 00:54:18.102
Speak to us!

409
00:54:26.308 --> 00:54:29.178
I am not an orator

410
00:54:29.179 --> 00:54:30.752
or a politician.

411
00:54:32.052 --> 00:54:33.689
I am a soldier.

412
00:54:36.155 --> 00:54:41.367
I have seen bravery
in men and women during war.

413
00:54:42.128 --> 00:54:43.897
And even once in this arena.

414
00:54:45.439 --> 00:54:47.164
So if you ask anything
of the gods...

415
00:54:49.069 --> 00:54:51.443
ask for that same bravery.

416
00:54:53.744 --> 00:54:55.876
Because Rome needs it now.

417
00:55:00.014 --> 00:55:02.882
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

418
00:55:02.883 --> 00:55:06.117
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

419
00:55:18.769 --> 00:55:21.329
From the South Gate.

420
00:55:21.330 --> 00:55:26.412
fighters from the stable
of Macrinus of Thysdrus!

421
00:55:38.954 --> 00:55:41.019
From the stables

422
00:55:41.020 --> 00:55:44.693
of Emperors Caracalla
and Geta themselves.

423
00:55:44.694 --> 00:55:47.355
the undefeated champion:

424
00:55:47.356 --> 00:55:51.095
Glyceo the Destroyer!

425
00:55:57.643 --> 00:55:58.674
Hold.

426
00:56:21.458 --> 00:56:23.293
Hold.

427
00:56:24.604 --> 00:56:26.197
Hail Caesars!

428
00:56:27.838 --> 00:56:31.300
Glyceo! Glyceo! Glyceo!

429
00:56:42.886 --> 00:56:46.150
Hold together
and when it charges.
break for the wall.

430
00:56:46.151 --> 00:56:47.086
Why should I?

431
00:56:51.323 --> 00:56:52.190
Hold!

432
00:56:53.358 --> 00:56:54.532
Hold!

433
00:56:54.533 --> 00:56:55.457
Break!

434
00:56:56.526 --> 00:56:57.833
Cowards!

435
00:57:11.847 --> 00:57:13.981
To the wall!

436
00:57:25.995 --> 00:57:27.026
Come on!

437
00:59:10.262 --> 00:59:13.199
Brother. it's that poet.
is it not?

438
00:59:14.004 --> 00:59:16.069
I can't remember.

439
00:59:16.070 --> 00:59:17.808
That night was a blur.

440
00:59:19.174 --> 00:59:21.910
"The gates of hell
are open night and day.

441
00:59:21.911 --> 00:59:25.078
Smooth the desc—"
I forget.

442
00:59:25.079 --> 00:59:26.850
"Smooth the descent..."

443
00:59:27.677 --> 00:59:29.754
"Smooth is the descent.

444
00:59:30.284 --> 00:59:31.987
easy is the way."

445
00:59:39.689 --> 00:59:40.699
Shield!

446
01:00:16.902 --> 01:00:20.398
Mercy! Mercy! Mercy!

447
01:00:22.237 --> 01:00:23.434
Blood.

448
01:00:26.505 --> 01:00:27.603
Lucilla.

449
01:00:28.309 --> 01:00:29.670
shall we show mercy?

450
01:00:29.671 --> 01:00:31.343
Mercy.

451
01:00:46.690 --> 01:00:48.722
No mercy!

452
01:00:48.723 --> 01:00:50.691
Your life has been
spared by the gods—

453
01:00:50.692 --> 01:00:54.773
I would sooner face your blade
than accept Roman mercy!

454
01:01:10.890 --> 01:01:14.352
Kill! Kill! Kill!

455
01:01:14.353 --> 01:01:17.554
Kill! Kill! Kill!

456
01:01:29.040 --> 01:01:34.010
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

457
01:02:02.106 --> 01:02:04.810
The road to freedom
doesn't run
through the arena.

458
01:02:05.604 --> 01:02:07.142
It leads to this.

459
01:02:11.643 --> 01:02:13.577
Go to your cells.

460
01:02:17.416 --> 01:02:20.991
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

461
01:02:37.867 --> 01:02:39.273
Come on. let's go.

462
01:02:52.486 --> 01:02:55.718
"Gates of hell
are open night and day.

463
01:02:56.721 --> 01:02:58.456
Smooth is the descent...

464
01:02:58.457 --> 01:03:00.393
easy is the way."

465
01:03:04.498 --> 01:03:06.970
<I>There. there. there. there.</I>

466
01:03:06.971 --> 01:03:08.367
<I>And I've got you.</I>

467
01:03:08.368 --> 01:03:11.041
<I>I'm Maximus.
the savior of Rome!</I>

468
01:03:30.590 --> 01:03:32.623
Scatto and Argento.

469
01:03:46.375 --> 01:03:47.737
Lucius is safe?

470
01:04:05.559 --> 01:04:06.624
Lucius!

471
01:04:19.309 --> 01:04:21.275
Lucius.

472
01:04:21.276 --> 01:04:24.279
you're the sole heir
to the throne now.

473
01:04:26.019 --> 01:04:27.413
There are men
who want to kill you

474
01:04:27.414 --> 01:04:28.910
so they can take power.

475
01:04:30.584 --> 01:04:33.881
I promise I'll bring you back
as soon as it's safe.

476
01:04:33.882 --> 01:04:37.588
Mother. why can't you
come with me?

477
01:04:37.589 --> 01:04:40.129
I... I have to
stay here for your sake.

478
01:04:40.130 --> 01:04:42.230
And for the sake of Rome.

479
01:04:42.231 --> 01:04:44.793
Remember who you are.

480
01:04:44.794 --> 01:04:46.697
And that I love you.

481
01:04:47.436 --> 01:04:48.798
I love you.

482
01:04:49.735 --> 01:04:50.767
Come.

483
01:04:54.003 --> 01:04:55.409
Give me your leg.

484
01:04:57.215 --> 01:04:59.016
Go. Go!

485
01:05:05.652 --> 01:05:07.157
So...

486
01:05:10.459 --> 01:05:11.887
What's your name?

487
01:05:14.659 --> 01:05:17.299
I'm Ravi. I'm a doctor.

488
01:05:18.500 --> 01:05:22.105
Because... more men die
of infected wounds

489
01:05:22.106 --> 01:05:24.669
than out there. in the arena.

490
01:05:26.035 --> 01:05:28.969
This needs to be cleaned.
it needs to be stitched and

491
01:05:28.970 --> 01:05:31.774
it is going to hurt.

492
01:05:31.775 --> 01:05:33.006
Mm.

493
01:05:33.007 --> 01:05:36.120
This is Devil's Breath
and opium.

494
01:05:36.716 --> 01:05:38.254
It's for the pain.

495
01:05:39.224 --> 01:05:40.916
You should breathe in.

496
01:05:46.891 --> 01:05:48.494
I've been here
so long now.

497
01:05:48.495 --> 01:05:51.024
I don't even notice anymore.

498
01:05:51.025 --> 01:05:53.830
I've done more amputations
than I can count.

499
01:05:54.998 --> 01:05:57.668
Where'd you
learn your trade?
Why do you ask?

500
01:05:57.669 --> 01:05:59.374
You've got a heavy hand.

501
01:06:00.740 --> 01:06:02.310
I used to be
a gladiator myself.

502
01:06:02.311 --> 01:06:03.773
Ah.

503
01:06:03.774 --> 01:06:05.973
And would you have bested me?

504
01:06:05.974 --> 01:06:07.514
In your prime. of course.

505
01:06:08.682 --> 01:06:11.418
In your current state.
I could best you now.

506
01:06:13.091 --> 01:06:16.423
Luckily for you.
I have put down my sword.

507
01:06:16.424 --> 01:06:18.722
So now I spend my days

508
01:06:18.723 --> 01:06:21.395
saving lives
instead of taking them.

509
01:06:22.826 --> 01:06:25.367
And why such a change
so late in life?

510
01:06:26.238 --> 01:06:28.501
What we do in life

511
01:06:28.502 --> 01:06:31.031
echoes in eternity.

512
01:06:34.609 --> 01:06:36.344
I feel like
I know those words.

513
01:06:36.345 --> 01:06:38.940
I can't take credit.

514
01:06:38.941 --> 01:06:41.613
It's written on
one of the tombs.

515
01:06:41.614 --> 01:06:44.385
Over the bones of a gladiator.

516
01:06:44.386 --> 01:06:45.815
My champion!

517
01:06:45.816 --> 01:06:48.081
I smell Devil's Breath!

518
01:06:50.425 --> 01:06:53.824
My... champion.

519
01:06:54.794 --> 01:06:56.563
Did you hear that crowd?

520
01:06:59.568 --> 01:07:01.766
Did you hear that crowd?
Mm-hm.

521
01:07:03.275 --> 01:07:05.934
You have something.
I knew it from the start.

522
01:07:05.935 --> 01:07:09.840
Did you now?
Yes. The Greeks call it...

523
01:07:10.645 --> 01:07:12.248
<I>thymos.</I>

524
01:07:12.249 --> 01:07:13.613
Smoke.

525
01:07:14.319 --> 01:07:15.681
Rage.

526
01:07:16.651 --> 01:07:18.750
That rage is your gift.

527
01:07:19.423 --> 01:07:22.291
Like the great Achilles.

528
01:07:22.292 --> 01:07:24.722
Never let it go.

529
01:07:24.723 --> 01:07:27.692
It will carry you
to greatness.

530
01:07:27.693 --> 01:07:29.497
my champion.

531
01:07:48.947 --> 01:07:51.078
Thank you

532
01:07:51.079 --> 01:07:53.113
for inviting me.

533
01:07:53.114 --> 01:07:55.160
This is truly an honor.

534
01:08:00.189 --> 01:08:02.199
I hear you are
the talk of the court.

535
01:08:04.468 --> 01:08:05.500
Yes.

536
01:08:06.371 --> 01:08:07.832
We've met before.

537
01:08:08.538 --> 01:08:10.571
Have we?
Long ago.

538
01:08:12.036 --> 01:08:13.672
Where?

539
01:08:13.673 --> 01:08:15.674
I was in the service
of your father's army

540
01:08:15.675 --> 01:08:17.776
on his African campaign.

541
01:08:18.977 --> 01:08:21.010
You served
with my father?

542
01:08:24.719 --> 01:08:25.850
Mm.

543
01:08:26.523 --> 01:08:28.556
I had the privilege

544
01:08:29.559 --> 01:08:31.261
of reading
his "Meditations."

545
01:08:31.262 --> 01:08:32.527
Mm.

546
01:08:35.499 --> 01:08:37.466
"The best revenge

547
01:08:38.568 --> 01:08:41.833
is to be unlike him
who performed the injury."

548
01:08:44.068 --> 01:08:46.705
I hear you've been
arming half the legions

549
01:08:46.706 --> 01:08:51.777
in the entire empire.
and here. now. in Rome...

550
01:08:53.077 --> 01:08:56.077
you're gaining influence
by sponsoring gladiators.

551
01:08:56.078 --> 01:08:58.288
I do it for the love
of the sport.

552
01:08:58.289 --> 01:09:01.325
And where did you find
these gladiators?

553
01:09:02.251 --> 01:09:05.054
They're usually
prisoners of war.

554
01:09:05.958 --> 01:09:09.530
Or vagrants.
Why do you ask?

555
01:09:09.531 --> 01:09:12.303
A man can choose to fight...

556
01:09:14.197 --> 01:09:15.899
and stay alive.

557
01:09:15.900 --> 01:09:19.068
It's the same in life as it is
in the arena. is it not?

558
01:09:21.545 --> 01:09:23.236
Who is this?

559
01:09:23.237 --> 01:09:25.679
That is my father
as a youth.

560
01:09:28.849 --> 01:09:30.177
<I>She had a child?</I>

561
01:09:30.178 --> 01:09:32.014
Mm.

562
01:09:32.015 --> 01:09:34.522
It's common knowledge.
When Commodus was killed.

563
01:09:34.523 --> 01:09:36.392
the boy disappeared.
Mm.

564
01:09:36.393 --> 01:09:38.559
But who would care?
Lucilla would care.

565
01:09:38.560 --> 01:09:41.266
More wine!
More wine!

566
01:09:42.599 --> 01:09:46.095
He was of the royal bloodline.
after all.

567
01:09:47.802 --> 01:09:49.196
And his father?

568
01:09:49.197 --> 01:09:54.036
Ostensibly.
Lucius Verus.

569
01:09:54.037 --> 01:09:55.906
See. it was
an arranged marriage.

570
01:09:55.907 --> 01:09:57.072
She was 14.

571
01:09:57.073 --> 01:10:00.548
Mm.
Females were not his taste.

572
01:10:00.549 --> 01:10:02.011
Nor mine. some days.
Nor yours!

573
01:10:03.552 --> 01:10:07.885
No. no. no.
By rumor. you see.
she took lovers.

574
01:10:07.886 --> 01:10:12.088
And by rumor.
the real father...
was Commodus.

575
01:10:13.025 --> 01:10:15.563
Brotherly love.
you see?
Yeah.

576
01:10:15.564 --> 01:10:17.258
If he died.

577
01:10:18.261 --> 01:10:20.766
there has to be remains.
Mm.

578
01:10:20.767 --> 01:10:24.198
And if he lived.
that would make him about...

579
01:10:24.199 --> 01:10:26.376
Um. well.
let's work it out.

580
01:10:26.377 --> 01:10:29.841
He was about 12
when he died?
Yes.

581
01:10:29.842 --> 01:10:34.176
So that would make him...

582
01:11:09.818 --> 01:11:10.685
My lady.

583
01:11:11.314 --> 01:11:12.181
Gracchus.

584
01:11:13.316 --> 01:11:15.184
Please come.
Thank you.

585
01:11:34.007 --> 01:11:35.380
Gladiator...

586
01:11:36.878 --> 01:11:37.877
do you know me?

587
01:11:46.283 --> 01:11:47.623
Do you have a family?

588
01:11:50.155 --> 01:11:53.398
A wife. Arishat.

589
01:11:54.929 --> 01:11:56.389
Arishat.

590
01:11:56.390 --> 01:11:59.701
She was killed
under your husband's command.

591
01:12:02.398 --> 01:12:04.606
Rome drowns
in its own blood.

592
01:12:04.607 --> 01:12:06.972
And yet you enjoy
the pleasures of the Colosseum.

593
01:12:08.272 --> 01:12:11.141
There is much
you do not understand.

594
01:12:17.952 --> 01:12:19.115
Lucius.

595
01:12:19.116 --> 01:12:21.282
I do not know
who you think I am.

596
01:12:23.595 --> 01:12:25.528
My name is Hanno.

597
01:12:25.529 --> 01:12:28.026
and I have no mother.
or none that I can remember.

598
01:12:34.738 --> 01:12:36.770
I'm so sorry.

599
01:12:36.771 --> 01:12:38.970
If your son were here.
I feel sure he would tell you

600
01:12:38.971 --> 01:12:41.005
not to grieve him.

601
01:12:41.006 --> 01:12:42.842
For he would not be the boy
that you sent away.

602
01:12:42.843 --> 01:12:44.845
That boy is dead.

603
01:12:47.245 --> 01:12:49.344
You may think
I have little worth.

604
01:12:50.985 --> 01:12:53.018
You may think
I betrayed you.

605
01:12:54.989 --> 01:12:56.791
But I need you to know...

606
01:12:58.190 --> 01:13:01.223
if you will not have
your mother's love.

607
01:13:01.224 --> 01:13:04.128
then take
your father's strength.

608
01:13:05.329 --> 01:13:06.735
You need it.

609
01:13:09.003 --> 01:13:13.236
His name was
Maximus Decimus Meridius.

610
01:13:14.613 --> 01:13:16.139
And I see him in you.

611
01:13:16.140 --> 01:13:17.548
Get out.

612
01:13:19.651 --> 01:13:22.146
My lady. we must go at once!

613
01:13:25.624 --> 01:13:28.085
Lucius. you were loved

614
01:13:28.086 --> 01:13:31.319
by myself
and by your father.

615
01:13:32.420 --> 01:13:33.992
Your name
was on his lips—

616
01:13:33.993 --> 01:13:35.830
Get out!

617
01:14:01.858 --> 01:14:03.792
Lucius is alive.

618
01:14:06.126 --> 01:14:07.993
Are you certain?

619
01:14:07.994 --> 01:14:09.325
Yes.

620
01:14:10.262 --> 01:14:11.602
I know my son.

621
01:14:14.673 --> 01:14:16.541
I spoke to him
tonight.

622
01:14:19.909 --> 01:14:23.009
He may be lost to me
for what I did.

623
01:14:24.243 --> 01:14:25.913
but he lives.

624
01:14:27.147 --> 01:14:29.817
The third day of the games
is tomorrow.

625
01:14:29.818 --> 01:14:31.478
Most fighters won't survive.

626
01:14:31.479 --> 01:14:32.887
Acacius.

627
01:14:34.253 --> 01:14:35.758
you must help him.

628
01:14:36.585 --> 01:14:38.486
Help him?
Yes.

629
01:14:40.996 --> 01:14:43.491
I failed him then.

630
01:14:44.032 --> 01:14:45.570
I know I did.

631
01:14:47.365 --> 01:14:49.464
I cannot fail him now.

632
01:14:52.106 --> 01:14:53.643
The army is in Ostia.

633
01:14:53.644 --> 01:14:56.503
If we wait a few days...

634
01:14:56.504 --> 01:14:58.583
He could be dead
by then.

635
01:15:00.609 --> 01:15:02.014
Acacius.

636
01:15:02.015 --> 01:15:05.656
I would willingly
give my life for Rome.

637
01:15:06.857 --> 01:15:09.253
but I will not
give my son's.

638
01:15:15.459 --> 01:15:17.734
And one.

639
01:15:18.561 --> 01:15:20.395
And two.

640
01:15:20.396 --> 01:15:23.200
And one.

641
01:15:23.201 --> 01:15:26.105
Together.
Timing. timing. timing!

642
01:15:27.405 --> 01:15:30.439
And one. And two.

643
01:15:31.112 --> 01:15:33.111
And one.

644
01:15:33.112 --> 01:15:35.081
Pause. pause!

645
01:15:37.921 --> 01:15:39.249
We won't get far
like this.

646
01:15:40.856 --> 01:15:43.319
Just him. You go.

647
01:15:43.320 --> 01:15:45.123
Go!

648
01:15:45.124 --> 01:15:48.666
Let's see how far you can go
on your own without your team.

649
01:15:50.395 --> 01:15:51.932
Ready?

650
01:15:51.933 --> 01:15:53.231
One!

651
01:15:54.102 --> 01:15:55.100
And two!

652
01:15:55.101 --> 01:15:57.235
Timing. timing!

653
01:15:57.941 --> 01:15:59.303
Come on. more!

654
01:16:04.607 --> 01:16:06.145
More!

655
01:16:23.032 --> 01:16:24.294
Leave him.

656
01:16:43.151 --> 01:16:46.548
It's just vinegar.
my friend.

657
01:16:48.517 --> 01:16:51.058
There will be
no more opium for you.

658
01:16:52.391 --> 01:16:56.128
There is plenty of pain waiting
for you in the next life.

659
01:16:56.129 --> 01:16:59.528
I don't know why
you are so greedy for it
in this one.

660
01:17:04.238 --> 01:17:05.742
Are you a free man. Ravi?

661
01:17:05.743 --> 01:17:07.602
"Free."

662
01:17:09.342 --> 01:17:11.814
I am. Mm.

663
01:17:11.815 --> 01:17:13.409
I laid down my sword

664
01:17:13.410 --> 01:17:15.510
and I swore never
to pick it up again.

665
01:17:15.511 --> 01:17:17.182
And yet
you choose this hell?

666
01:17:17.183 --> 01:17:18.887
Mm-hm.

667
01:17:18.888 --> 01:17:20.252
What was your home before?

668
01:17:21.519 --> 01:17:22.990
Varanasi.

669
01:17:22.991 --> 01:17:25.355
And why don't you go back?

670
01:17:25.356 --> 01:17:26.895
I wish I could.

671
01:17:26.896 --> 01:17:28.656
But...

672
01:17:31.199 --> 01:17:33.232
I met a woman.
Ah.

673
01:17:34.103 --> 01:17:36.564
It's always a woman.
Always.

674
01:17:36.565 --> 01:17:40.634
She is from Londinium.
Britannia. You know.

675
01:17:40.635 --> 01:17:42.537
So now...

676
01:17:42.538 --> 01:17:45.573
our sons.
they speak only Latin.

677
01:17:45.574 --> 01:17:48.081
My daughter's eyes.
they are as blue as yours.

678
01:17:50.746 --> 01:17:52.382
We are Romans now.

679
01:17:52.383 --> 01:17:56.090
I grew up hearing stories
at my grandfather's knee.

680
01:17:57.258 --> 01:18:00.589
He used to talk
of the dream that was Rome.

681
01:18:02.901 --> 01:18:06.870
It was so fragile.
you could only whisper it...

682
01:18:09.138 --> 01:18:10.940
or it would vanish.

683
01:18:11.800 --> 01:18:13.370
So.

684
01:18:13.371 --> 01:18:15.108
what was this dream?

685
01:18:15.109 --> 01:18:19.707
A Rome where all could live
under fair law and be protected.

686
01:18:20.644 --> 01:18:22.545
A Rome of the Senate.

687
01:18:24.153 --> 01:18:25.713
A Rome of hope.

688
01:18:28.784 --> 01:18:33.225
Your grandfather.
he sounds like
a dangerous man.

689
01:18:33.226 --> 01:18:34.458
Hm.

690
01:18:37.166 --> 01:18:39.462
The odds are against you.

691
01:18:41.665 --> 01:18:43.731
The odds
are always against me.

692
01:18:44.668 --> 01:18:45.941
Don't worry. old man.

693
01:18:45.942 --> 01:18:47.877
Eh?

694
01:18:51.279 --> 01:18:53.444
You should
get some rest. Hm?
Mm.

695
01:18:54.513 --> 01:18:56.986
Your men will need you
to lead them tomorrow.

696
01:19:13.301 --> 01:19:15.037
This is about survival.

697
01:19:16.139 --> 01:19:17.566
Survive!

698
01:19:17.567 --> 01:19:21.438
In the name of Poseidon.

699
01:19:21.439 --> 01:19:25.673
we celebrate the glory
of naval war.

700
01:19:25.674 --> 01:19:27.510
They have archers.

701
01:19:27.511 --> 01:19:30.084
Be ready.
Listen for my commands.

702
01:19:30.085 --> 01:19:32.889
Stay together
and pull as one. yes?

703
01:19:32.890 --> 01:19:33.846
Yes!

704
01:19:33.847 --> 01:19:36.223
Yes?
Yes!

705
01:19:43.067 --> 01:19:45.858
Today we relive

706
01:19:45.859 --> 01:19:49.499
the Battle of Salamis!

707
01:19:50.666 --> 01:19:55.308
The Trojans
versus the Persians!

708
01:19:59.842 --> 01:20:01.413
Oars out!
Oars!

709
01:20:02.185 --> 01:20:04.349
And... pull!

710
01:20:23.899 --> 01:20:26.008
Archers!

711
01:20:26.009 --> 01:20:26.944
Archers!

712
01:20:29.080 --> 01:20:30.112
Pull!

713
01:20:39.024 --> 01:20:40.814
Pull!

714
01:20:43.488 --> 01:20:44.489
Pull!

715
01:20:57.733 --> 01:21:00.142
Pull! To my time!

716
01:21:00.903 --> 01:21:02.210
And... now!

717
01:21:04.808 --> 01:21:07.247
Left side! Ready. and

718
01:21:07.248 --> 01:21:09.282
ship oars now!

719
01:21:09.283 --> 01:21:11.417
Oars in! Oars in!

720
01:21:12.915 --> 01:21:13.782
Get down!

721
01:21:29.965 --> 01:21:33.966
And pull! And pull!

722
01:21:36.640 --> 01:21:38.938
Don't stop!

723
01:21:41.117 --> 01:21:42.447
Pull!

724
01:21:44.980 --> 01:21:46.419
And right!

725
01:21:52.020 --> 01:21:53.557
Ready to ram!

726
01:21:55.659 --> 01:21:58.298
And brace! Brace!

727
01:22:38.242 --> 01:22:39.670
Everyone regroup!

728
01:23:15.904 --> 01:23:17.939
Praetorians!

729
01:23:19.283 --> 01:23:21.843
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

730
01:23:21.844 --> 01:23:22.877
Move. move.

731
01:23:29.722 --> 01:23:32.986
In the name of the emperors...

732
01:23:32.987 --> 01:23:37.596
the victor is Hanno!

733
01:23:49.280 --> 01:23:51.214
Who did this?

734
01:23:53.944 --> 01:23:56.153
Who did this?

735
01:23:56.815 --> 01:23:59.078
It was me!
I did it!

736
01:23:59.079 --> 01:24:00.982
I did it! I did it! I did it!
It was me!

737
01:24:05.560 --> 01:24:07.659
Geta will want retribution
for all of you.

738
01:24:08.728 --> 01:24:10.023
Did you learn to shoot
in the same place

739
01:24:10.024 --> 01:24:11.596
you learned to recite poetry?

740
01:24:11.597 --> 01:24:12.828
Be glad it wasn't me.

741
01:24:12.829 --> 01:24:14.302
or that arrow
would have found you.

742
01:24:30.046 --> 01:24:31.518
Be seated.

743
01:24:34.017 --> 01:24:35.456
I have news for you.

744
01:24:39.957 --> 01:24:41.429
He's here. sir.

745
01:24:44.498 --> 01:24:46.533
Oh. still here.

746
01:24:48.667 --> 01:24:50.162
Macrinus.

747
01:24:50.163 --> 01:24:52.341
Welcome.

748
01:24:53.872 --> 01:24:56.278
Yes. I'm listening.

749
01:24:56.279 --> 01:24:58.940
You know
this is my house now.

750
01:24:58.941 --> 01:25:01.349
Your debt to me is
over 10.000 denarii.

751
01:25:01.350 --> 01:25:02.812
You know that.

752
01:25:02.813 --> 01:25:05.518
I have other things. Uh...

753
01:25:05.519 --> 01:25:07.421
Cattle. Art!

754
01:25:07.422 --> 01:25:09.115
Truth. then.

755
01:25:09.116 --> 01:25:10.787
What do you... want?

756
01:25:10.788 --> 01:25:13.526
Truth.
That's what I want.

757
01:25:13.527 --> 01:25:18.026
Nothing happens in Rome
without your knowledge.

758
01:25:19.161 --> 01:25:21.205
You have
the senators' trust.

759
01:25:22.032 --> 01:25:24.306
You have
Lucilla's trust.

760
01:25:24.307 --> 01:25:27.035
More importantly.
you have my trust.

761
01:25:29.072 --> 01:25:33.106
You wish my... loyalty?

762
01:25:33.107 --> 01:25:34.779
I own...

763
01:25:36.211 --> 01:25:38.144
your house.

764
01:25:38.145 --> 01:25:40.818
I want your loyalty.

765
01:25:44.560 --> 01:25:45.988
I...

766
01:25:47.189 --> 01:25:49.023
Tell me.
I have heard...

767
01:25:49.024 --> 01:25:51.730
of a plot...

768
01:25:52.601 --> 01:25:55.370
to dethrone the emperors.
Yes.

769
01:25:55.371 --> 01:25:57.900
But the plan
has been delayed. uh...

770
01:25:57.901 --> 01:26:01.167
A gladiator is to be rescued
from the arena.

771
01:26:01.168 --> 01:26:02.674
Tonight.
Mm.

772
01:26:02.675 --> 01:26:05.810
I don't know why.
I know why. I know who.

773
01:26:08.210 --> 01:26:09.286
Pack.

774
01:26:12.918 --> 01:26:14.456
Quickly.

775
01:26:42.310 --> 01:26:43.583
Open up!

776
01:27:03.606 --> 01:27:05.671
Open for
the emperors' guard!

777
01:27:33.130 --> 01:27:36.604
My Lady. come with us.

778
01:28:21.915 --> 01:28:24.211
Thanks to the civic virtue

779
01:28:24.212 --> 01:28:26.885
of men like Thraex
and Macrinus.

780
01:28:28.185 --> 01:28:29.888
your insurrection

781
01:28:30.594 --> 01:28:32.561
has been revealed.

782
01:28:34.422 --> 01:28:35.762
The honor.

783
01:28:36.864 --> 01:28:40.734
the dignitas that Rome
has bestowed upon you...

784
01:28:43.200 --> 01:28:46.332
all this you have forfeited
by your treachery.

785
01:28:46.333 --> 01:28:48.302
Please. Emperor Geta.

786
01:28:49.008 --> 01:28:50.876
Torture me if you want.

787
01:28:51.780 --> 01:28:53.207
but do not lecture me.

788
01:28:53.208 --> 01:28:56.717
Your name
will be forgotten!

789
01:28:57.786 --> 01:29:00.853
Lost... to history.

790
01:29:02.791 --> 01:29:04.251
You are damned.
General.

791
01:29:06.927 --> 01:29:08.894
You laugh.
You damn me?

792
01:29:09.996 --> 01:29:11.764
I don't care.

793
01:29:11.765 --> 01:29:15.394
Everything is forgotten in time.
Empires fall. So do emperors.

794
01:29:15.395 --> 01:29:17.198
Why wait?

795
01:29:17.199 --> 01:29:20.509
I will gut him right now!
No. no. no!

796
01:29:20.510 --> 01:29:23.875
Let them be. Come! Come!

797
01:29:23.876 --> 01:29:25.778
His death must be public.

798
01:29:25.779 --> 01:29:27.373
Public?

799
01:29:27.374 --> 01:29:30.343
Hang his entrails
from the city gates!

800
01:29:30.344 --> 01:29:31.950
And crucify her!

801
01:29:32.656 --> 01:29:34.215
Crucify her!

802
01:29:34.216 --> 01:29:36.217
Take them away!

803
01:29:36.218 --> 01:29:39.628
Shh! Shh! Shh!

804
01:29:52.775 --> 01:29:53.939
Thank you. Macrinus.

805
01:30:00.277 --> 01:30:01.617
Come on.

806
01:30:05.018 --> 01:30:06.951
In these last days.

807
01:30:06.952 --> 01:30:10.284
I have come to think of you
not as a subject

808
01:30:10.285 --> 01:30:12.594
but as a true friend.

809
01:30:12.595 --> 01:30:14.321
Thank you.

810
01:30:14.322 --> 01:30:17.093
Thank you so much.
But as a friend.

811
01:30:17.094 --> 01:30:19.931
I must counsel caution.

812
01:30:19.932 --> 01:30:22.968
Acacius is a hero of Rome.

813
01:30:23.806 --> 01:30:27.334
Crucifixion
is for thieves.

814
01:30:27.335 --> 01:30:28.512
Christians.

815
01:30:29.647 --> 01:30:32.680
It's too common.
He is a traitor.
He must die.

816
01:30:32.681 --> 01:30:34.143
I agree.

817
01:30:34.144 --> 01:30:39.919
Let the gods decide
his fate in the Colosseum.

818
01:30:46.323 --> 01:30:47.960
Let the gods decide.

819
01:30:50.734 --> 01:30:54.769
You know. last night I woke.
dreaming of a dark river.

820
01:30:56.333 --> 01:30:58.332
This time.
for the first time.

821
01:30:58.333 --> 01:30:59.873
I was crossing it.

822
01:31:00.678 --> 01:31:02.369
Hm.

823
01:31:02.370 --> 01:31:04.976
Well. you know.
where I come from.

824
01:31:04.977 --> 01:31:08.045
crossing a river.
it represents forgiveness.

825
01:31:08.046 --> 01:31:11.147
Represents... salvation.

826
01:31:11.148 --> 01:31:14.315
Where I come from.
it means
you're already dead.

827
01:31:22.524 --> 01:31:25.063
But as I saw it.
I was not afraid.

828
01:31:26.770 --> 01:31:28.494
For...

829
01:31:28.495 --> 01:31:31.399
For someone was waiting
for me on the other side.

830
01:31:33.040 --> 01:31:34.776
There.

831
01:31:45.052 --> 01:31:46.590
Who is this man?

832
01:31:47.923 --> 01:31:49.384
Scratched out?

833
01:31:50.288 --> 01:31:52.321
Maximus.

834
01:31:55.095 --> 01:31:57.095
I saw him fight once.

835
01:31:58.131 --> 01:31:59.767
He was magnificent.
Mm.

836
01:31:59.768 --> 01:32:02.836
Yeah. My time in the arena.
it was after his.

837
01:32:02.837 --> 01:32:07.203
but many still talked of him
in whispers. you know?

838
01:32:07.204 --> 01:32:09.437
Spoke of him.

839
01:32:10.242 --> 01:32:12.010
What he did.

840
01:32:12.011 --> 01:32:13.947
I met him once.

841
01:32:15.753 --> 01:32:17.280
He was kind.

842
01:32:19.581 --> 01:32:21.449
He bowed to no one.

843
01:32:24.927 --> 01:32:26.618
Come with me.

844
01:32:26.619 --> 01:32:29.699
Hmm?
Come. With me.

845
01:32:48.786 --> 01:32:53.051
When a rebel gladiator dies.
we bury them here.

846
01:32:53.052 --> 01:32:57.485
"What we do in life
echoes in eternity."

847
01:33:15.175 --> 01:33:17.108
This is Argento.

848
01:33:17.109 --> 01:33:18.682
This is Scatto.

849
01:33:59.054 --> 01:34:00.724
Cheers.

850
01:34:01.386 --> 01:34:02.825
And stop.

851
01:34:04.422 --> 01:34:08.555
For his treason
against the lives

852
01:34:08.556 --> 01:34:12.724
of the emperors
and the Roman state.

853
01:34:12.725 --> 01:34:16.168
General Justus Acacius.

854
01:34:17.534 --> 01:34:20.567
an enemy of the people!

855
01:34:20.568 --> 01:34:23.174
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

856
01:34:23.175 --> 01:34:25.573
We love you. Acacius!
You are a hero!

857
01:34:26.884 --> 01:34:30.016
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

858
01:35:01.347 --> 01:35:04.116
<I>Vae victis.</I>
General.

859
01:35:26.073 --> 01:35:28.042
Acacius!

860
01:35:29.276 --> 01:35:33.541
Acacius! Acacius! Acacius!

861
01:35:39.451 --> 01:35:43.486
From the vanquished city
of Numidia.

862
01:35:44.654 --> 01:35:49.964
the victor of two conquests
in the Colosseum...

863
01:35:49.965 --> 01:35:52.528
Go now. <I>Vae victis.</I>

864
01:35:56.831 --> 01:35:59.765
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

865
01:35:59.766 --> 01:36:02.174
Hanno!

866
01:36:02.175 --> 01:36:05.078
Oh. Lord. any honor I have.

867
01:36:05.079 --> 01:36:06.838
I will give it to you!
It's too late.

868
01:36:06.839 --> 01:36:10.215
The Roman traitor or

869
01:36:10.216 --> 01:36:12.548
the barbarian hero.

870
01:36:13.320 --> 01:36:15.154
Let the gods decide.

871
01:36:15.155 --> 01:36:16.893
Lucius... wait.

872
01:36:18.358 --> 01:36:19.653
Wait! Wait!

873
01:36:29.532 --> 01:36:32.337
I am a vessel.

874
01:36:33.670 --> 01:36:35.912
Fill me with vengeance

875
01:36:36.871 --> 01:36:39.113
and vanquish the betrayer.

876
01:36:56.924 --> 01:36:59.232
We love you. Acacius!
Move it!

877
01:37:03.337 --> 01:37:05.039
Pick it up!

878
01:37:05.040 --> 01:37:07.503
Bravo. Hanno!

879
01:37:07.504 --> 01:37:09.043
We love you. Acacius!

880
01:37:09.044 --> 01:37:10.110
What are you waiting for?

881
01:37:10.111 --> 01:37:11.243
You will die!

882
01:37:42.143 --> 01:37:43.474
I know who you are.

883
01:37:45.280 --> 01:37:47.313
Lucius Verus Aurelius.

884
01:38:00.590 --> 01:38:02.625
Acacius
has raised his hand!

885
01:38:03.628 --> 01:38:06.001
He has surrendered.

886
01:38:13.506 --> 01:38:15.506
Let the gods decide.

887
01:38:33.097 --> 01:38:35.955
The gods have rendered
their judgment.

888
01:38:39.103 --> 01:38:40.564
Do what you must.

889
01:38:41.666 --> 01:38:44.106
But on my death.
you have to know...

890
01:38:45.934 --> 01:38:47.868
I love your mother.
Lucilla.

891
01:38:49.344 --> 01:38:50.706
And your father...

892
01:38:53.480 --> 01:38:54.512
Maximus.

893
01:38:55.812 --> 01:38:58.009
I would have died
for him.

894
01:38:58.010 --> 01:38:59.978
Kill him!

895
01:38:59.979 --> 01:39:02.718
Let him live!
Please!

896
01:39:03.820 --> 01:39:06.887
Live! Live! Live! Live!

897
01:39:13.863 --> 01:39:15.566
Kill him!

898
01:39:17.537 --> 01:39:18.535
Kill him!

899
01:39:18.536 --> 01:39:19.866
Archers!

900
01:39:19.867 --> 01:39:21.802
No!
Kill him!

901
01:39:21.803 --> 01:39:24.442
Acacius! Acacius!

902
01:39:24.443 --> 01:39:26.213
Kill him!

903
01:39:26.214 --> 01:39:29.249
Kill him! Kill him!

904
01:39:31.351 --> 01:39:32.715
Acacius!

905
01:39:42.859 --> 01:39:43.858
No!

906
01:39:44.465 --> 01:39:46.024
No!

907
01:39:46.025 --> 01:39:47.697
Acacius!

908
01:39:50.240 --> 01:39:52.305
Damn you!

909
01:39:54.143 --> 01:39:56.035
Death will be
too good for you!

910
01:40:01.581 --> 01:40:04.747
Is this how Rome
treats its heroes?

911
01:40:08.753 --> 01:40:10.258
Tell me!

912
01:40:12.361 --> 01:40:16.956
If his life has no value.
what are yours worth?

913
01:40:16.957 --> 01:40:22.093
The gods have spoken!

914
01:40:35.978 --> 01:40:39.650
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

915
01:40:55.096 --> 01:40:58.141
For our own safety.
we should return to the palace.

916
01:41:06.481 --> 01:41:09.680
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

917
01:41:19.360 --> 01:41:21.791
Stay back! Stay back!

918
01:42:09.971 --> 01:42:14.415
Arishat!

919
01:42:31.962 --> 01:42:33.533
We had a bargain.

920
01:42:37.165 --> 01:42:40.506
I gave him to you.
You let him live.

921
01:42:40.507 --> 01:42:42.233
And you got
what you wanted.

922
01:42:42.234 --> 01:42:44.939
I always get what I want.
Why did you let him live?

923
01:42:44.940 --> 01:42:47.877
You bought a gladiator.
not a slave.

924
01:42:49.584 --> 01:42:51.386
My will is my own.

925
01:42:53.588 --> 01:42:55.048
Ah...

926
01:42:55.049 --> 01:42:57.820
How blue is your blood?

927
01:42:57.821 --> 01:43:00.493
Perhaps the heart of a Roman

928
01:43:00.494 --> 01:43:02.760
beats in that chest.

929
01:43:08.438 --> 01:43:11.372
The greatest temple
Rome ever built.

930
01:43:11.373 --> 01:43:13.000
The Colosseum.

931
01:43:13.001 --> 01:43:15.409
Because this is
what they believe in.

932
01:43:15.410 --> 01:43:17.103
Power.

933
01:43:17.104 --> 01:43:19.908
They gather here to watch
the strong strike down the weak.

934
01:43:19.909 --> 01:43:21.811
There has to be
something else.
There is nothing else.

935
01:43:21.812 --> 01:43:24.683
There has to be
another Rome.
There is no other Rome.

936
01:43:26.214 --> 01:43:27.850
The "dream"?
Mm.

937
01:43:27.851 --> 01:43:29.852
The dream of Rome?

938
01:43:29.853 --> 01:43:31.426
It's an old man's fantasy.

939
01:43:33.188 --> 01:43:34.594
Who are you?

940
01:43:37.632 --> 01:43:40.666
What was your name
before you traded it
for a Roman one?

941
01:43:41.702 --> 01:43:43.163
You'll never know.

942
01:43:45.970 --> 01:43:47.607
I have a destiny.

943
01:43:51.074 --> 01:43:53.448
The gods delivered you to me.

944
01:43:56.453 --> 01:43:58.210
You will be my instrument.

945
01:43:58.211 --> 01:44:01.555
I will never be
your instrument.
in this life or the next.

946
01:44:09.829 --> 01:44:13.028
That will not be my destiny.

947
01:44:15.032 --> 01:44:16.767
But I will see your end.

948
01:44:37.690 --> 01:44:39.658
What else could I do?

949
01:44:39.659 --> 01:44:41.528
He and his bitch
were plotting to kill us.

950
01:44:41.529 --> 01:44:44.289
Don't you hear them?
They're calling for our heads!

951
01:44:44.290 --> 01:44:46.401
The Praetorians
will put down this crowd.

952
01:44:46.402 --> 01:44:48.227
Like they have every other.
You brought this on us.

953
01:44:48.228 --> 01:44:50.736
Filthy ape!

954
01:44:54.368 --> 01:44:57.170
Perhaps you should. uh.

955
01:44:57.171 --> 01:45:01.582
take Dondus elsewhere
to comfort him?

956
01:45:11.154 --> 01:45:13.429
Forgive
my brother's outburst.

957
01:45:15.290 --> 01:45:16.893
The disease
that infects his loins

958
01:45:16.894 --> 01:45:18.928
has spread to his brain.

959
01:45:18.929 --> 01:45:22.031
Every day he gets worse.
I will reason with him.

960
01:45:38.379 --> 01:45:41.555
I see you.

961
01:45:41.556 --> 01:45:43.624
I see you.

962
01:45:44.990 --> 01:45:47.253
Caracalla. Caracalla!

963
01:45:47.254 --> 01:45:48.958
Come on. stand up.

964
01:45:48.959 --> 01:45:51.158
Get up. get up.
Not you.

965
01:45:51.159 --> 01:45:52.963
All right.
there you go.

966
01:45:54.703 --> 01:45:57.065
Now. listen to me.

967
01:45:57.066 --> 01:45:58.737
What's the matter?

968
01:45:58.738 --> 01:46:01.509
Nothing's ever mine.

969
01:46:01.510 --> 01:46:03.907
Everything is ours. always.

970
01:46:03.908 --> 01:46:07.142
Even in the womb...
he tried...

971
01:46:07.980 --> 01:46:11.376
to cut my umbilicus

972
01:46:11.377 --> 01:46:13.279
so that I couldn't have
any more air.

973
01:46:13.280 --> 01:46:15.655
You remember that.
do you?
Certainly.

974
01:46:15.656 --> 01:46:18.086
Come. sit.
One cannot forget.

975
01:46:18.087 --> 01:46:20.418
My conscience compels me.

976
01:46:20.419 --> 01:46:21.958
What?

977
01:46:21.959 --> 01:46:23.256
Sit.

978
01:46:23.257 --> 01:46:24.665
Your brother

979
01:46:25.536 --> 01:46:27.063
means to blame you

980
01:46:28.066 --> 01:46:30.505
in front of
the entire Senate...

981
01:46:30.506 --> 01:46:31.968
But I did not do it!

982
01:46:31.969 --> 01:46:33.640
for what's happening
in the streets.

983
01:46:33.641 --> 01:46:36.104
The chaos!
He's lying!

984
01:46:36.105 --> 01:46:38.007
No testimony
can be more damning

985
01:46:38.008 --> 01:46:41.582
than one brother
against another.

986
01:46:41.583 --> 01:46:44.310
That's a lie!
He always lies!

987
01:46:44.311 --> 01:46:46.884
He can be very persuasive.

988
01:46:46.885 --> 01:46:49.656
So?
What will they do to me?

989
01:46:49.657 --> 01:46:52.527
Oh. I don't dare imagine.
But imagine this:

990
01:46:52.528 --> 01:46:54.629
What will they do to Dondus?

991
01:46:57.766 --> 01:47:00.634
What will they do

992
01:47:00.635 --> 01:47:02.097
to Dondus?

993
01:47:04.397 --> 01:47:05.706
It's your decision.

994
01:47:43.537 --> 01:47:44.404
Brother.

995
01:47:48.047 --> 01:47:49.881
Put down the blade.

996
01:47:49.882 --> 01:47:51.080
You lie.

997
01:47:51.081 --> 01:47:52.983
Give it to me.
You always lie!

998
01:47:52.984 --> 01:47:54.017
Give it—

999
01:47:57.857 --> 01:48:00.188
Look at me.
Look at me. Look at me.

1000
01:48:00.189 --> 01:48:02.696
Lie!
Listen to me.
Break the spell.

1001
01:48:02.697 --> 01:48:04.797
Lie!
Break the spell!

1002
01:48:04.798 --> 01:48:07.999
I've always protected you.
Because I love you.

1003
01:48:08.639 --> 01:48:10.705
Come back. Help me.

1004
01:48:33.323 --> 01:48:34.729
Lucius.

1005
01:48:56.445 --> 01:48:59.115
Never could have imagined
the fates would lead us here.

1006
01:49:01.151 --> 01:49:02.988
And yet here we are.

1007
01:49:04.651 --> 01:49:06.452
Everything has
brought us full circle.

1008
01:49:06.453 --> 01:49:09.620
You sent me away
and yet fate

1009
01:49:09.621 --> 01:49:12.162
brought me back
to the very ground
where he died.

1010
01:49:15.167 --> 01:49:16.166
This ring...

1011
01:49:18.071 --> 01:49:19.774
belonged to my father.

1012
01:49:23.813 --> 01:49:26.945
He gave it
to your father.
Maximus.

1013
01:49:26.946 --> 01:49:28.849
as a token of trust.

1014
01:49:30.248 --> 01:49:33.216
I gave it to Acacius
for his valor.

1015
01:49:37.728 --> 01:49:39.959
This ring belonged to my wife.

1016
01:49:42.931 --> 01:49:44.392
I shall wear it next to yours.

1017
01:49:58.672 --> 01:50:01.145
I am truly sorry for Acacius.

1018
01:50:02.412 --> 01:50:05.280
I could not see the man.

1019
01:50:07.417 --> 01:50:09.318
He was a soldier of Rome.

1020
01:50:11.289 --> 01:50:12.651
There was a plan.

1021
01:50:13.962 --> 01:50:15.356
He was readying troops
at Ostia

1022
01:50:15.357 --> 01:50:18.491
under the command
of Darius Sextus.

1023
01:50:18.492 --> 01:50:21.561
Troops he was to lead
against the emperors.

1024
01:50:23.598 --> 01:50:28.007
Acacius. Maximus.
Marcus Aurelius.

1025
01:50:29.142 --> 01:50:31.505
They lived and died
for Rome.

1026
01:50:32.211 --> 01:50:33.672
We all do.

1027
01:50:35.709 --> 01:50:38.083
Is it true
they intend to kill you?

1028
01:50:41.020 --> 01:50:43.153
One man or another
has had a sword
against my neck

1029
01:50:43.154 --> 01:50:45.519
since the day
my father died.

1030
01:50:48.722 --> 01:50:50.733
But now
that I've found you.

1031
01:50:51.560 --> 01:50:53.362
it doesn't matter.

1032
01:50:54.728 --> 01:50:56.529
I am not afraid.

1033
01:50:56.530 --> 01:50:59.632
I've become well versed
in losing the things
that I love.

1034
01:51:02.505 --> 01:51:03.811
But now that I've found you.

1035
01:51:03.812 --> 01:51:05.670
I have no desire
to lose you again.

1036
01:51:08.709 --> 01:51:10.918
You stand like him.
Mm.

1037
01:51:11.679 --> 01:51:13.052
Alert.

1038
01:51:13.923 --> 01:51:15.054
Proud.

1039
01:51:17.256 --> 01:51:19.828
I do not have his strength.

1040
01:51:20.754 --> 01:51:22.897
I wish that were true.

1041
01:51:24.263 --> 01:51:27.461
I wish I were telling you
to flee this place.

1042
01:51:36.209 --> 01:51:37.307
Go now.

1043
01:51:45.614 --> 01:51:46.789
Strength and honor.

1044
01:51:49.288 --> 01:51:50.958
Strength and honor.

1045
01:52:03.564 --> 01:52:05.763
As Emperor.

1046
01:52:05.764 --> 01:52:07.436
I have convened

1047
01:52:08.373 --> 01:52:11.670
the Senate to appoint
my First Consul

1048
01:52:11.671 --> 01:52:15.113
and bestow upon him the power
to administer the military

1049
01:52:15.114 --> 01:52:18.381
and civic functions
of the Empire.

1050
01:52:22.255 --> 01:52:23.617
I name...

1051
01:52:24.719 --> 01:52:27.257
Citizen Dondus!

1052
01:52:34.168 --> 01:52:35.838
Hail Dondus!

1053
01:52:39.272 --> 01:52:40.766
Hail Dondus!

1054
01:52:42.737 --> 01:52:45.506
Hail Dondus.
Hail Dondus!

1055
01:52:45.507 --> 01:52:48.048
Hail Dondus!

1056
01:52:52.285 --> 01:52:54.153
As Second Consul...

1057
01:52:56.058 --> 01:52:57.552
I name...

1058
01:52:59.963 --> 01:53:01.226
Citizen...

1059
01:53:03.527 --> 01:53:04.966
Macrinus!

1060
01:53:07.333 --> 01:53:10.663
Hail Macrinus!

1061
01:53:10.664 --> 01:53:12.633
Hail Macrinus!

1062
01:53:14.472 --> 01:53:17.109
There will be
a triumphal parade
to celebrate.

1063
01:53:17.110 --> 01:53:18.672
There will be games

1064
01:53:19.411 --> 01:53:21.476
and mass executions.

1065
01:53:24.548 --> 01:53:27.252
Long live the Empire!

1066
01:53:28.816 --> 01:53:30.650
Long live the Empire!

1067
01:53:30.651 --> 01:53:32.356
Long live the Empire!

1068
01:53:38.727 --> 01:53:39.935
Sit down.

1069
01:53:43.336 --> 01:53:46.040
I happen to have...

1070
01:53:49.573 --> 01:53:53.278
with good fortune
and not a little skill...

1071
01:53:55.018 --> 01:53:58.184
the remaining emperor's ear.

1072
01:54:05.358 --> 01:54:07.622
I can speak logic to it...

1073
01:54:12.398 --> 01:54:14.893
and tame the madness
in the street. But...

1074
01:54:17.865 --> 01:54:19.469
to restore order...

1075
01:54:21.539 --> 01:54:23.407
I must have power...

1076
01:54:27.116 --> 01:54:29.149
and command

1077
01:54:29.844 --> 01:54:31.811
over the Praetorian Army.

1078
01:54:37.720 --> 01:54:39.456
Ballot...

1079
01:54:41.625 --> 01:54:42.998
or hand?

1080
01:54:45.134 --> 01:54:47.662
Aye!
Aye!

1081
01:54:50.964 --> 01:54:52.601
Your humble servant.

1082
01:54:56.706 --> 01:54:58.277
Put your hands down.

1083
01:55:00.941 --> 01:55:02.446
You can sit down.

1084
01:55:15.989 --> 01:55:17.626
<I>Rome must fall.</I>

1085
01:55:20.334 --> 01:55:22.367
I need only
give it a push.

1086
01:55:25.438 --> 01:55:27.636
And after Rome falls...

1087
01:55:28.540 --> 01:55:30.969
what then?

1088
01:55:33.116 --> 01:55:35.149
You are
your father's child.

1089
01:55:37.120 --> 01:55:40.648
His dream of Rome
was never a dream.

1090
01:55:40.649 --> 01:55:42.782
It was a fiction.

1091
01:55:42.783 --> 01:55:45.158
"The best revenge is

1092
01:55:45.159 --> 01:55:49.129
to become unlike the one
who did the injury."

1093
01:55:49.130 --> 01:55:54.200
I have made myself
unlike your father.

1094
01:55:54.201 --> 01:55:57.830
He spoke of dreams.
I speak of truth.

1095
01:55:57.831 --> 01:56:00.339
And the only truth
in my Rome

1096
01:56:01.870 --> 01:56:03.903
is the law
of the strongest.

1097
01:56:06.215 --> 01:56:07.577
I was owned

1098
01:56:09.042 --> 01:56:10.580
by an emperor.

1099
01:56:13.552 --> 01:56:15.684
Now I control an empire.

1100
01:56:16.720 --> 01:56:20.018
Where else but in Rome
can a man do that?

1101
01:56:25.267 --> 01:56:29.830
Do you recognize
your father's mark on me?

1102
01:56:34.606 --> 01:56:35.935
If there is anything

1103
01:56:36.641 --> 01:56:38.036
you need...

1104
01:56:39.743 --> 01:56:41.446
in these last hours.

1105
01:56:42.416 --> 01:56:44.119
we will provide.

1106
01:56:49.786 --> 01:56:52.556
Your death will clear my path
to the throne.

1107
01:56:54.428 --> 01:56:57.461
Tomorrow
there will be games.

1108
01:56:57.462 --> 01:56:59.134
And at them...

1109
01:56:59.994 --> 01:57:01.730
I will prevail.

1110
01:57:15.350 --> 01:57:16.844
Ravi!

1111
01:57:23.424 --> 01:57:25.753
Can you get me a message
to Ostia by morning?

1112
01:57:25.754 --> 01:57:27.590
What is in Ostia?

1113
01:57:27.591 --> 01:57:29.087
There is an army.

1114
01:57:31.300 --> 01:57:33.057
I'm asking you
to risk yourself. my friend.

1115
01:57:33.058 --> 01:57:35.269
in the service
of something greater.

1116
01:57:38.131 --> 01:57:39.570
Ride to Ostia.

1117
01:57:40.804 --> 01:57:42.968
Take this ring
to General Darius Sextus.

1118
01:57:42.969 --> 01:57:44.443
Are you listening?

1119
01:57:45.039 --> 01:57:47.775
Darius Sextus.

1120
01:57:47.776 --> 01:57:49.844
He will know it
as Acacius's ring.

1121
01:57:52.783 --> 01:57:54.948
And. uh.

1122
01:57:55.819 --> 01:57:57.192
who shall I say has

1123
01:57:57.854 --> 01:57:59.557
sent me with this ring?

1124
01:58:02.925 --> 01:58:05.299
I am Lucius Verus Aurelius.

1125
01:58:06.500 --> 01:58:08.027
The Prince of Rome.

1126
01:58:09.272 --> 01:58:10.798
Tell him
I am summoning the army

1127
01:58:10.799 --> 01:58:13.131
to the defense
of a new Republic.

1128
01:58:21.779 --> 01:58:23.074
Should I trust you?
Yes.

1129
01:58:23.075 --> 01:58:25.187
Should I?
Yes.

1130
01:58:32.053 --> 01:58:34.790
Ravi! I need your keys.

1131
01:58:40.864 --> 01:58:42.567
Thank you.

1132
01:59:20.409 --> 01:59:22.871
Stop! Come back!

1133
01:59:53.607 --> 01:59:54.771
Who gave you this?

1134
01:59:55.741 --> 01:59:57.906
Lucius Verus Aurelius.

1135
01:59:59.107 --> 02:00:00.381
The Prince of Rome.

1136
02:00:53.502 --> 02:00:56.602
Must we kill Lucilla?

1137
02:00:58.166 --> 02:01:01.970
Until she dies.
you will never know peace.

1138
02:01:03.842 --> 02:01:04.874
Ever.

1139
02:01:15.722 --> 02:01:18.392
The people love her.
Her death will incite the mob.

1140
02:01:18.393 --> 02:01:21.054
If she dies and the streets
rise up in anger.

1141
02:01:21.055 --> 02:01:22.660
I shall deliver them
Caracalla's head

1142
02:01:22.661 --> 02:01:24.156
and the people
shall acclaim me.

1143
02:01:24.157 --> 02:01:27.831
That. my friend.
is politics.

1144
02:01:30.605 --> 02:01:32.506
Shall we?
Yes.

1145
02:01:47.721 --> 02:01:49.853
Today will be
your last fight. champion.

1146
02:01:50.922 --> 02:01:52.592
And our master
has bestowed on you...

1147
02:01:54.926 --> 02:01:57.355
the wooden sword of freedom.

1148
02:02:01.295 --> 02:02:03.393
But you have to
earn it first.

1149
02:02:03.394 --> 02:02:05.836
Today. you're gonna
defend your mother.

1150
02:02:28.694 --> 02:02:31.598
Wood or steel.
a point is still a point!

1151
02:02:58.825 --> 02:03:00.385
Wait for me.

1152
02:03:19.175 --> 02:03:20.976
In honor

1153
02:03:20.977 --> 02:03:25.409
of the acclamation
of Emperor Caracalla.

1154
02:03:25.410 --> 02:03:31.448
First Consul Dondus
and Second Consul Macrinus.

1155
02:03:31.449 --> 02:03:36.090
and as punishment
for her conspiracy
against the empire.

1156
02:03:36.091 --> 02:03:40.666
for her calumnies against
the emperor's imperial bloodline

1157
02:03:40.667 --> 02:03:42.998
and for fomenting
military mutiny

1158
02:03:42.999 --> 02:03:44.604
along with her husband.

1159
02:03:44.605 --> 02:03:48.333
the queen will face
divine justice

1160
02:03:48.334 --> 02:03:52.514
at the hands
of the Praetorian Guard.

1161
02:04:16.969 --> 02:04:18.496
I am not a general.

1162
02:04:20.170 --> 02:04:23.710
But we are all soldiers.

1163
02:04:25.681 --> 02:04:27.504
And up until now.

1164
02:04:27.505 --> 02:04:31.882
we have fought for nothing more
than another day's survival.

1165
02:04:31.883 --> 02:04:33.786
What will you
have us do?

1166
02:04:35.086 --> 02:04:36.381
Well. you can return
to your cells

1167
02:04:36.382 --> 02:04:38.515
if you do not wish
to fight this battle.

1168
02:04:38.516 --> 02:04:40.892
Or...

1169
02:04:42.588 --> 02:04:43.994
you can join me.

1170
02:04:45.228 --> 02:04:47.700
And fight for a freedom
far beyond these walls.

1171
02:04:47.701 --> 02:04:49.361
Aye!

1172
02:04:49.362 --> 02:04:53.608
There once was a time when
honor meant something in Rome.

1173
02:04:55.271 --> 02:04:56.809
In this Rome

1174
02:04:57.713 --> 02:04:59.910
I no longer believe
that exists.

1175
02:04:59.911 --> 02:05:02.011
We must find it!

1176
02:05:04.179 --> 02:05:05.917
And know this:

1177
02:05:07.217 --> 02:05:11.021
Where death is. we are not.

1178
02:05:12.959 --> 02:05:14.926
Where we are.

1179
02:05:15.621 --> 02:05:17.390
death is not!

1180
02:05:20.395 --> 02:05:21.702
By my sword.

1181
02:05:23.563 --> 02:05:25.364
Strength and honor.

1182
02:05:25.365 --> 02:05:27.399
Strength and honor!

1183
02:05:27.400 --> 02:05:31.074
Strength and honor!

1184
02:05:55.771 --> 02:05:57.935
Let it not be said

1185
02:05:57.936 --> 02:06:01.136
that the emperor
is not merciful.

1186
02:06:01.137 --> 02:06:06.746
The queen will be granted
a single gladiator

1187
02:06:06.747 --> 02:06:10.607
to defend her against
the Praetorian Guard.

1188
02:06:20.521 --> 02:06:24.588
The champion. Hanno!

1189
02:06:28.364 --> 02:06:31.937
Hanno! Hanno! Hanno!

1190
02:07:37.497 --> 02:07:39.268
Yes!

1191
02:07:43.439 --> 02:07:45.340
Summon the cavalry.
Put this down at once.

1192
02:07:46.816 --> 02:07:49.245
This is war! Real war!

1193
02:07:54.153 --> 02:07:57.583
The army of Acacius
is advancing
just outside of Rome. sir.

1194
02:08:00.225 --> 02:08:01.718
We can still
outflank them.

1195
02:08:01.719 --> 02:08:04.128
They have only
5.000 troops. no more.

1196
02:08:05.461 --> 02:08:07.031
How many are we?

1197
02:08:07.032 --> 02:08:08.461
Six thousand.
Perhaps more.

1198
02:08:08.462 --> 02:08:10.232
Ride to the gate
and hold them.

1199
02:09:01.957 --> 02:09:03.022
Filthy scum!

1200
02:09:16.862 --> 02:09:18.433
Lucius!

1201
02:09:20.173 --> 02:09:21.238
Give me the bow.

1202
02:09:45.033 --> 02:09:47.626
Go. my son. Lucius—

1203
02:09:47.627 --> 02:09:48.825
Shh-sh-sh-sh...

1204
02:09:48.826 --> 02:09:50.365
Horse!

1205
02:11:23.065 --> 02:11:25.229
Will nothing
kill this barbarian?

1206
02:11:25.230 --> 02:11:27.825
My name is
Lucius Verus Aurelius!

1207
02:11:27.826 --> 02:11:30.300
A man does not become
emperor by bloodline alone.

1208
02:11:30.301 --> 02:11:33.138
It must be taken by force
and kept by force.

1209
02:11:33.139 --> 02:11:35.074
Are you such a man
as this?

1210
02:11:35.075 --> 02:11:36.603
I don't fight for power.

1211
02:11:36.604 --> 02:11:39.441
I fight to free Rome
from men like you

1212
02:11:39.442 --> 02:11:41.047
and to return it to them.

1213
02:11:41.048 --> 02:11:43.940
The gods themselves
want Rome reborn.

1214
02:11:43.941 --> 02:11:46.976
They sent me...
to fulfill that task.

1215
02:11:46.977 --> 02:11:50.650
And what if your gods
sent me here to kill you?

1216
02:11:50.651 --> 02:11:51.718
Huh?

1217
02:11:52.853 --> 02:11:55.193
It's time to end this. Macrinus!

1218
02:12:31.166 --> 02:12:33.397
Hah!

1219
02:13:03.229 --> 02:13:04.758
Strength and honor.

1220
02:13:05.365 --> 02:13:06.892
my son.

1221
02:14:40.262 --> 02:14:41.987
You look to me to speak.

1222
02:14:44.156 --> 02:14:45.924
I know not what
to say other than

1223
02:14:45.925 --> 02:14:47.993
we have all known
too much death.

1224
02:14:49.194 --> 02:14:52.767
Let no more blood be spilt
in the name of tyranny.

1225
02:14:56.674 --> 02:14:59.278
My grandfather.
Marcus Aurelius.

1226
02:14:59.279 --> 02:15:02.183
talked of a dream
that would be Rome.

1227
02:15:03.175 --> 02:15:05.076
A dream that my father.

1228
02:15:06.321 --> 02:15:09.178
Maximus Decimus Meridius.

1229
02:15:09.179 --> 02:15:10.785
died for.

1230
02:15:11.986 --> 02:15:13.623
An ideal.

1231
02:15:16.331 --> 02:15:20.761
A city for the many
and a refuge
for those in need.

1232
02:15:20.762 --> 02:15:23.270
A home worth fighting for.

1233
02:15:24.372 --> 02:15:28.704
A home that Maximus
spent his life defending.

1234
02:15:30.741 --> 02:15:32.609
That dream is lost.

1235
02:15:38.551 --> 02:15:40.221
But dare we...

1236
02:15:41.719 --> 02:15:44.390
rebuild that dream
together?

1237
02:15:56.261 --> 02:15:58.063
What say you?

1238
02:16:04.412 --> 02:16:06.280
Aye!

1239
02:16:07.415 --> 02:16:08.744
Aye!

1240
02:16:09.450 --> 02:16:10.745
Aye!

1241
02:16:10.746 --> 02:16:15.179
Aye! Aye! Aye! Aye!

1242
02:17:19.850 --> 02:17:21.080
Mother.

1243
02:18:13.640 --> 02:18:15.838
Speak to me. Father.
